                            <comment id="13195847" author="tlipcon" created="Sun, 29 Jan 2012 21:15:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a test case which shows the issue. We tracked it down to a JNI issue &amp;#8211; if when using libhdfs, the thread that started the JVM isn&apos;t the same thread that first uses libhdfs, it will fail with the error described in the JIRA. The fix as committed solves the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
